    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Portable canopies used in processions to shelter a monarch, dignitary, holy person, or object. In Catholic ceremonies, such canopies are used to shelter the Blessed Sacrament, the holy oils on Holy Thursday, relics, or a statue.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000049836/Thesaurus del corredo ecclesiastico [online] (1999)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079245/Catholic Encyclopedia [online] (2003-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Baldacchino mobile utilizzato per le processioni che viene posto sopra il SS. Sacramento, gli oli santi del Giovedì Santo, le reliquie, una statua o un alto dignitario. È sovente costituito da una armatura retta da aste (quattro, sei o otto aste) ricoperta di tessuto (guarnizione del baldacchino processionale).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Italian</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000049836/Thesaurus del corredo ecclesiastico [online] (1999)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dais mobile utilisé pour les processions et pouvant abriter le Saint Sacrement, les Saintes Huiles le Jeudi Saint, des reliques, une statue ou un haut dignitaire. Il est souvent constitué d'une armature portée par quatre, six ou huit hampes et recouvert par une garniture de dais de procession.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>French</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000049836/Thesaurus del corredo ecclesiastico [online] (1999)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Estructura móvil utilizada para las procesiones, es puesta sobre el Santísimo Sacramento, los santos óleos del Jueves Santo, las reliquias, una escultura o un alto dignatario. Con frecuencia está constituida por una armadura sostenida con astas (cuatro, seis u ocho) y cubierta de tela (guarnición del dosel procesional).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000049836/Thesaurus del corredo ecclesiastico [online] (1999)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Draagbare baldakijnen die men gebruikt tijdens processies om een heilig persoon of object te beschermen. Bij katholieke ceremonies hangt men dergelijke baldakijnen boven het Heilige Sacrament, de heilige oliën op Witte Donderdag, relikwieën of een beeld.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>列隊行進間用以遮蔽聖人或聖物的可攜式頂蓬。在天主教儀式中，此頂蓬則被用於遮蔽聖體、濯足節聖油，聖骨、或雕像。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
